President Obama announced his intention to nominate Rose Gottemoeller for the position of Assistant Secretary of State for Verification and Compliance. The President emphasized the importance of addressing the threat of nuclear weapons and strengthening the international non-proliferation regime. Gottemoeller, who has a background in defense and nuclear issues in Russia and the former Soviet states, has held positions at the Carnegie Moscow Center and the Carnegie Endowment. She has also served in various roles in the U.S. Department of Energy and the National Security Council, focusing on non-proliferation and national security.